Etymology 1[edit]

From legō (“I read, gather”) +‎ -tō (frequentative suffix).

Verb[edit]

lēctō (present infinitive lēctāre, perfect active lēctāvī, supine lēctātum); first conjugation

  1. (rare) Synonym of lēctitō

Etymology 2[edit]

See the etymology of the main entry.

Participle[edit]

lēctō

  1. dative masculine singular of lēctus
  2. dative neuter singular of lēctus
  3. ablative masculine singular of lēctus
  4. ablative neuter singular of lēctus

Etymology 3[edit]

Noun[edit]

lectō

  1. dative singular of lectus
  2. ablative singular of lectus
